### Customizing Skills

Each skill file served by Gisia can be overridden per-project by committing a replacement Markdown file into the repository. When a custom file is present, Gisia serves it directly instead of the default generated content.

**File locations (relative to repo root):**

| Skill | Repo path |
|-------|-----------|
| Project | `.gisiabot/skills/project.md` |
| Issues | `.gisiabot/skills/issues.md` |
| Epics | `.gisiabot/skills/epics.md` |
| Labels | `.gisiabot/skills/labels.md` |
| Branches | `.gisiabot/skills/branches.md` |
| Tags | `.gisiabot/skills/tags.md` |
| Merge Requests | `.gisiabot/skills/merge_requests.md` |
| Pipelines | `.gisiabot/skills/pipelines.md` |
| Jobs | `.gisiabot/skills/jobs.md` |
| Members | `.gisiabot/skills/members.md` |
| Comments | `.gisiabot/skills/comments.md` |

**Example — override the issues skill:**

```bash
mkdir -p .gisiabot/skills
# Write your custom instructions into the file
echo "# Custom Issues Skill" > .gisiabot/skills/issues.md
git add .gisiabot/skills/issues.md
git commit -m "Add custom issues skill"
git push
```

Once pushed, `<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/<%= @project.full_path %>/-/issues/skill.md` will return your custom file instead of the default.

To revert to the default, delete the file and push:

```bash
git rm .gisiabot/skills/issues.md
git commit -m "Remove custom issues skill"
git push
```

