### Access the Git Repository via SSH

Use SSH to clone or interact with this repository. An SSH key must be registered in your Gisia account settings.

**Clone:**
```bash
git clone <%= @project.ssh_url_to_repo %>
```

**Configure your Git identity (first time only):**
```bash
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "you@example.com"
```

**Push a new repository:**
```bash
git checkout -b main
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git push -u origin main
```

**Push an existing repository:**
```bash
cd existing-repo
git remote add origin <%= @project.ssh_url_to_repo %>
git push -u origin --all
git push -u origin --tags
```

---

### Access the Git Repository via Personal Access Token

You can clone this repository over HTTPS using a personal access token as the password. Embed the token directly in the URL:

```bash
git clone https://<username>:<personal_token>@<%= URI.parse(@project.http_url_to_repo).host %>/<%= @project.full_path %>.git
```

Note that embedding the token in the URL will store it in your shell history. For a more secure approach, omit the token and enter it when prompted:

```bash
git clone <%= @project.http_url_to_repo %>
```

When Gisia asks for your password, provide your personal access token instead of your account password.

**Push to the repository:**

The same credentials work for pushing. Set the remote with the token embedded, then push as usual:

```bash
cd your-repo
git remote set-url origin https://<username>:<personal_token>@<%= URI.parse(@project.http_url_to_repo).host %>/<%= @project.full_path %>.git
git push origin HEAD
```

